\p{It turns out, all the information which was really interesting was encoded in the "structure-preserving transformations" between them. (That was the bulk of our time spent studying [[ela]] and [[ila]], after all!)}
\p{We can form an abstraction describing this situation where we have a [gadget] and [transformations] between them: this is category theory.}
